A man has been arrested by the Kwara State Police Command for allegedly killing his father, identified as Michael Olagunju, and selling his body parts to some ritualists. It was learnt that the deceased was murdered on his farm at Kajola, Odo-Owa in the Oke-Ero Local Government Area of the state by his son who connived with some ritualists to remove Olagunju’s body parts, including his two hands and his heart. Confirming the incident to newsmen, the spokesperson of the state police command, Ajayi Okasanmi, said a discreet investigation has begun into the case. He added that only one suspect has been arrested in connection to the murder. “A farmer was killed on his farm at Kajola in Odo-Owa last week. One suspect has been arrested in connection with the crime. “The Commissioner of Police, CP Mohammed Bagega, has ordered a discreet Investigation into the case,” Okasanmi said.